<font color="#FF0000">IN THE STORIES</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct  2 23:25:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Lets suppose that PTSD has a cause.  From this cause we manifest certain sysmtoms.  Let us again suppose that everyone does not have the same symptoms.<br><br>
Could it be that the causes are not the same for us all.  Should we not explore the complexity of our emotions and beliefs together so we may be more aware of the &quot;Why&quot;.  Those who read may see something that brings them closer to the truth.<br><br>
I for one am with the Cook, Ed, Art, and the other risk takers.  What have we got to lose.  This site was meant to break new ground.  I don't come here to read library excerpts.<br><br>
We should not forget that images created from the stories told here speak louder than hollow rhetoric.
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


